{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/jagracey/Awesome-Unicode/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","descriptionHTML":"<div>\n<g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"joy\" fallback-src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f602.png\">😂</g-emoji> <g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"ok_hand\" fallback-src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f44c.png\">👌</g-emoji> A curated list of delightful Unicode tidbits, packages and resources.</div>","description":":joy: :ok_hand: A curated list of delightful Unicode tidbits, packages and resources."},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-29T11:37:27.953Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Quirks and Troubleshooting</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>String length is typically determined by counting codepoints.</strong> This means that surrogate pairs would count as two characters. Combining multiple diacritics may be stacked over the same character. <code>a + ̈  == ̈a   </code>, increasing length, while only producing a single character.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:04:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Quirks and Troubleshooting</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Similarily, reversing strings often is a non-trivial task.</strong> Again, surrogate pairs and diacritics must be reversed together. <a href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/esrever\">ES Reverser</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/esrever\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">790</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":790,\"repo\":\"mathiasbynens/esrever\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> provides a pretty good solution.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:04:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Quirks and Troubleshooting</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Upper and lower case mappings are not always one-to-one.</strong> They can also be:\n<ul>\n<li>One-to-many: (ß → SS )</li>\n<li>Contextual: (…Σ ↔ …ς AND …ΣΤ… ↔ …στ… )</li>\n<li>Locale-sensitive: ( I ↔ ı AND İ ↔ i )</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:04:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode9.0.0/\">Version 9.0.0</a> (Latest Version, August 2016 - adds exactly 7,500 characters)</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T17:58:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode8.0.0/\">Version 8.0.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T17:58:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Awesome Packages &#x26; Libraries</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/LuminosoInsight/python-ftfy\">python-ftfy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/LuminosoInsight/python-ftfy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2957,\"repo\":\"LuminosoInsight/python-ftfy\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Given Unicode text, make its representation consistent and possibly less broken.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-13T17:48:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Awesome Packages &#x26; Libraries</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vim-utils/vim-troll-stopper\">vim-troll-stopper</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vim-utils/vim-troll-stopper\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">160</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":160,\"repo\":\"vim-utils/vim-troll-stopper\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Stop Unicode trolls from messing with your code.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-13T17:48:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>More Reading</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://kunststube.net/encoding/\">What Every Programmer Absolutely, Positively Needs To Know About Encodings And Character Sets To Work With Text</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-13T17:02:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://shapecatcher.com/\">Shapecatcher</a> - Draw the character you're looking for.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-03T00:37:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Awesome Packages &#x26; Libraries</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/esrever\">ESReverser</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/esrever\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">790</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":790,\"repo\":\"mathiasbynens/esrever\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A Unicode-aware string reverser written in JavaScript.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-02T05:56:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Awesome Packages &#x26; Libraries</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/reinderien/mimic\">mimic</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/reinderien/mimic\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3624,\"repo\":\"reinderien/mimic\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - [ab]using Unicode to create tragedy</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-02T05:56:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Myths of Unicode</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Unicode is simply a 16-bit code</strong> - Some people are under the misconception that Unicode is simply a 16-bit code where each character takes 16 bits and therefore there are 65,536 possible characters. This is not, actually, correct. It is the single most common myth about Unicode, so if you thought that, don't feel bad.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Myths of Unicode</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>You can use any unassigned codepoint for internal use</strong> - No. Eventually that hole will be filled with a different character. Instead use private use or noncharacters.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Myths of Unicode</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Every Unicode code point represents a character</strong> - No. There are lots of nonCharacters (FFFE, FFFF, 1FFFE,…)</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Awesome Packages &#x26; Libraries</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jagracey/PhantomScript\">PhantomScript</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jagracey/PhantomScript\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">33</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":33,\"repo\":\"jagracey/PhantomScript\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - 👻 🔦 Invisible JavaScript code execution &#x26; social engineering</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Emojis</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/emoji/charts/full-emoji-list.html\">Unicode Consortium's Emoji Chart</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Emojis</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://emojipedia.org/\">Emojipedia</a> - Information about specific emoji, news blog.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Emojis</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://emojitracker.com/\">emojitracker</a> - Realtime emoji use on Twitter.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":