notes/javascript-unicode\">JavaScript has a Unicode Problem</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>More Reading</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://labs.spotify.com/2013/06/18/creative-usernames/\">Creative usernames and Spotify account hijacking</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://unicode.org/cldr/utility/confusables.jsp?r=None\">Confusable Unicode Characters</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/ucd/\">Unicode Character Database</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dumps.codepoints.net/\">Database Dumps of Codepoints.net</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/Public/UCD/latest/ucd/Blocks.txt\">Unicode Blocks List</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/charts/index.html\">Unicode Character Code Charts</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/charts/case/\">Unicode Case Charts</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/charts/normalization/\">Unicode Normalization Chart</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Exploring Deeper into Unicode Yourself</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/faq/\">Unicode FAQ</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Universal repertoire</strong> \t - Every writing system ever used shall be respected and represented in the standard</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Logical order</strong> \t\t - In bidirectional text are the characters stored in logical order, not in a way that the representaion</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Efficiency</strong>\t\t\t - The documentation must be efficient and complete.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Unification</strong>\t\t\t - Where different cultures or languages use the same character, it shall be only included once. This point is</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Characters, not glyphs</strong> - Only characters, not glyphs shall be encoded. In a nutshell, glyphs are the actual graphical</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Dynamic composition</strong>\t - New characters can be composed of other, already standardized characters. For example, the character “Ä” can be composed of an “A” and a dieresis sign (“ ¨ ”).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Semantics</strong>\t\t\t\t - Included characters must be well defined and distinguished from others.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Stability</strong>\t\t\t\t - Once defined characters shall never be removed or their codepoints reassigned. In the case of an error, a codepoint shall be deprecated.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Plain Text</strong>\t\t\t - Characters in the standard are text and never mark-up or metacharacters.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/standard/principles.html\">Principles of the Unicode Standard</a></h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Convertibility</strong>\t\t - Every other used encoding shall be representable in terms of a Unicode encoding.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode7.0.0/\">Version 7.0.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode6.3.0/\">Version 6.3.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode6.2.0/\">Version 6.2.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode6.1.0/\">Version 6.1.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode6.0.0/\">Version 6.0.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode5.2.0/\">Version 5.2.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode5.1.0/\">Version 5.1.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li>Version 5.0.0 (unavailable)</li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode4.0.1/\">Version 4.0.1</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/corrigendum5.html\">Version 4.0.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-06-01T05:21:17.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/mfornos/awesome-microservices","repo":"mfornos/awesome-microservices"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","repo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints"}},"pageContext":{"repo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","id":"awesomes/github.com/jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/mfornos/awesome-microservices","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/Codepoints/awesome-codepoints"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","3289010534"]}